description:
&lt;p&gt;Come and work with a fantastic team and be supported and encouraged to develop within your role as a Band 5 Staff Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Leyland ward is an outstanding elective 25 bedded Orthopaedic area which provides elective surgery for planned joint replacements, spinal procedures/ surgery and day case patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have a brilliant forward thinking team, who will all welcome and support you, including a fabulous Enhanced Recovery Practitioner who has supported the team in achieving discharging patients who have had total knee or hip replacement surgery in going home the same day, and this is the first unit in the region to have accomplished and maintained this in the whole region, to which the team are very proud. There is a wider multi-disciplinary team with a strong and supportive presence on the ward incorporating Physiotherapists, Occupational Therapists, pharmacists and a Discharge Facilitator who are always happy to share their knowledge to enable you to build on yours.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The supportive nature of the team as a whole shows in our excellent appraisal and friends and family feedback, and is reflected in our recent achievement of silver in our STAR audit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ward is incorporated within the Surgical Unit and there is a wide range of learning opportunities within the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be encouraged and fully supported to develop within your potential and beyond and be part of a friendly and welcoming team - a team that consistently achieves the best for our patients and relatives as well as for each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is for 22.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: To be confirmed&lt;/p&gt;
